Linville MILLER, Appellant, v. A. C. ADERHOLD, Warden, United States Penitentiary, Atlanta, Georgia, Appellee. No. 6759. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Oct. 15, 1932. Linville Miller, in pro. per. Clint W. Hager, U. S. Atty., and Hal Lindsay, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Atlanta, Ga., for appellee.

Before BRYAN, SIBLEY, and WALKER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On the authority of Prussian v. United States, 282 U. S. 675, 51 S. Ct. 223, 75 L. Ed. 610, the judgment is affirmed.
